        </button>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">
          Our relocation partners with us and gives free consultations to users
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Housing in Lausanne Is Challenging -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mb-4">
            The Challenge
          </span>
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
            Why Housing in Lausanne Is <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-600 to-primary-700 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Challenging</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
            University culture, lakeside appeal, and startup energy create strong housing demand
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">University & Research Demand</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              EPFL (École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne) and UNIL (University of Lausanne) bring thousands of international students, researchers, and academic staff annually. Student housing supply cannot meet demand, pushing students and young academics into private market apartments. Popular areas near campuses (Renens, Ecublens) see constant turnover each academic year. PhD students and postdocs often secure better apartments, creating competition with young professionals. Research grants and fellowships provide housing budgets, maintaining price pressure.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Startup & Tech Scene Growth</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Lausanne's growing startup ecosystem (EPFL Innovation Park, Flon district tech companies, biotech sector) attracts young professionals and entrepreneurs. The Swiss Tech Convention Center and proximity to Geneva create international business appeal. Startup employees often prefer Lausanne Centre and Flon areas, driving up rents in trendy neighborhoods. Corporate relocations from tech companies add to housing pressure. Younger demographic competes aggressively for modern apartments near coworking spaces and vibrant nightlife.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 21v-4m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6.5l1 1H21l-3 6 3 6h-8.5l-1-1H5a2 2 0 00-2 2zm9-13.5V9" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Lakeside Premium Housing</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Lake Geneva (Lac Léman) shoreline properties in Ouchy and Pully command premium rents (CHF 2,200-3,500+ for 2.5-3.5 rooms, up to CHF 6,000 for luxury lakeside). Families and corporate expats compete for these high-quality apartments with lake views, waterfront access, and excellent amenities. Limited lakefront supply means apartments rarely become available. Waiting lists exist for the best buildings. International Olympic Committee (IOC) presence in Lausanne adds diplomatic and sports organization demand for premium housing.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 5h12M9 3v2m1.048 9.5A18.022 18.022 0 016.412 9m6.088 9h7M11 21l5-10 5 10M12.751 5C11.783 10.77 8.07 15.61 3 18.129" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">French-Language Barrier</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Lausanne is in French-speaking Canton de Vaud. Most rental contracts, landlord communication, and administrative processes are in French. Non-French speakers struggle with dossier preparation, contract understanding, and landlord negotiations. English is less common than in Zurich or Geneva's international sectors. University students get some English support, but private market requires French or professional translation. Missing French-language nuances can disqualify applications or lead to unfavorable lease terms. Agencies provide critical French-language navigation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Academic Year Timing Pressure</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Late August through September sees intense housing competition as students arrive for EPFL/UNIL academic year. Apartments that became available over summer are snapped up immediately. New students compete against returning students upgrading housing. Families relocating for corporate jobs also target September moves for school year starts. This creates annual housing crunch with landlords receiving 15-25 applications per apartment. Non-academic relocations should avoid August-September timing when possible. Early preparation (3-4 months ahead) essential for September moves.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 via-white to-red-50 rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary-100">
